As the COVID-19 numbers continue to drop, Durbanites have wasted no time getting out of their homes to take advantage of relaxed lockdown regulations. Tourism authorities say it's going to take some time before the impact of COVID-19 can be reversed. eNCA's Dasen Thathiah takes us along the Durban promenade. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Durbanites have wasted no time getting out of their homes to take advantage of relaxed lockdown regulations. But tourism authorities say it's going to take some time before the impact of COVID-19 can be reversed. READ: SA's first weekend under Level 2 lockdown KwaZulu-Natal has over 22,800 confirmed cases of COVID-19 and is still reporting hundreds of new cases daily. Under the new regulations, a maximum of 50 people are allowed at funerals, weddings, gyms, swimming pools, bars, taverns, shebeens, cinemas, theatres and concert venues. READ: Denosa: KZN lacks clear COVID-19 plan Inter-provincial travelling around South Africa and water-based tourism activities are also allowed under Level 2 regulations. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.